Avian botulism has killed more than 40,000 birds at the Klamath Refuge in the past year — the worst outbreak in 40 years.

Here's a look into the rescue mission.

text:
Had the Kentucky Derby been run as scheduled May 2, Tiz the Law would have been the favorite off of his authoritative victories in the Holy Bull Stakes and Florida Derby.

But the four-month coronavirus delay only bolstered the horse's resume.

https://t.co/Zha8sRdFg9

text: It’s a strange time for restaurant tipping, a vague American custom that has only gotten vaguer with the extreme conditions of the pandemic, writes @hooleil. https://t.co/aTnqu8Bbvm

text: This year's Inside Lands virtual music festival attracted more than 3.2 million unique viewers over the two-day event, according to data released by Twitch. Here's what those numbers mean for future online concerts. https://t.co/CswFT78iYu

text: Officials with the Uptown Nightclub in Oakland announced Friday afternoon the club will not reopen after being closed for six months because of the coronavirus pandemic. https://t.co/afJMnftyuJ

text:

text: Oakland A’s minor-league coach Webster Garrison spent two months on a ventilator in the hospital after contracting COVID-19. He got married to his longtime partner while in the hospital and the couple is now preparing for a new life together. https://t.co/9ltaqtp9nO

text:
